article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay 88, S. Dakota St. 81
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- Rahmon Fletcher scored 29 points off the bench and Mike Schachtner added 19 points as Wisconsin-Green Bay beat South Dakota State 88-81 on Saturday. Fletcher made 12 of 14 shots from the field and was perfect on four free throws for the Phoenix (5-2), who trailed until the closing seconds of the first half. Fletcher is averaging 10.5 points. Randy Berry's buzzer-beater at the end of the first half helped the Phoenix overcome a 10-point deficit in the closing minutes and gave Wisconsin-Green Bay a 40-39 lead. The Phoenix shot 63 percent from the field in the second half and made six of 10 3-point attempts to maintain the lead. The Phoenix shot 59 percent overall. Berry chipped in 13 points and Troy Cotton added 12 for Wisconsin-Green Bay. SDSU (3-3) built a lead early on the strength of its 3-point shooting. The Jackrabbits made five of their first seven 3-point attempts to take a 26-18 lead with just over nine minutes to play in the first half. They finished the game 9-for-18. Ben Beran led the Jackrabbits in scoring with 20 points. Kai Williams had 17 points and seven rebounds, and Garrett Callahan added 13 points and six assists. Wisconsin-Green Bay leads the all-time series 3-0.
